reviews.text: Recommended this place by my family from Sacramento since we are just visiting from Seattle. Found out the owners can speak Tagalog! The white sauce chicken pizza was delicious. Super hospitable and friendly people, would come back again :)

The owner and his son are amazing. Made my son's birthday a memorable experience with great hospitality. We all had a blast and will be back for future occasions! Food was superb! Kids loved the pizza and wings! We had to keep on ordering :)  Thank you and see you again!

I‚Äôve been coming here since I moved to Rancho in 2018, and it‚Äôs hands down the best local pizza spot. The prices are fair, the portions are generous, and the flavor never disappoints. I believe they may have changed ownership recently, but the quality has stayed consistent, which says a lot. I also appreciate the occasional discount texts they send out. This place has earned my continued support, and if you‚Äôre in the area looking for great pizza at a solid price, you won‚Äôt be disappointed.

Delicious, hot, pizza, and wings. The man at the cashier was extremely nice and came over to our table and talked to us about collage, computers, and pizza! It was a very clean atmosphere, and the crust on the pizza was very good as well as their ranch.

The party size pizza was worth it - delicious and enough to feed a group of hungry 8 adults. The buffalo chicken wings was scrumptious and our server was so gracious and cheerful and surprised us all by speaking Tagalog üòÑ

detailedReviews.author: Cayla Vargas
detailedReviews.text: No one helped us. We rang the bell, as instructed by their hand written sign and the two people in the back seemingly ignored us. We waited in there for a bit, talking loudly to get someone's attention, but nothing. No one else was in there and they were open for several more hours, so I'm not sure why we weren't helped. While we were standing there, we saw shoes piled up by the door to the back. Not really a clean look. We ended up walking out and going to a different restaurant. Maybe put a bell in the front door, so you know when someone walks in. It's also a safety hazard for your workers.

detailedReviews.text: Ordered a combo pizza thru Uber Eats. detailedReviews.text:
Pizaa was absolutely amazing. I am glad I got it to go. Although staff was very nice the woman running the register was coughing badly and most of the tables were dirty or covered in dirty plates. Please try this local place and take your pizza to go. You will not be sorry!!! Its really good pizza!!!
